    "dom_section_identifier": "nice-cataracts-adults-ng77-2025-section-0025",
    "position": 24,
    "paragraph_or_text_span": "For people who have not had previous corneal refractive surgery, use 1 of the following to calculate the intraocular lens power before cataract surgery: If the axial length is less than 22.00 mm, use Haigis or Hoffer Q. If the axial length is between 22.00 and 26.00 mm, use Barrett Universal II if it is installed on the biometry device and does not need the results to be transcribed by hand. Use S",
